pathHint:
Used together with Path Templating, where the parameter value is actually part
    of the operation's URL. This does not include the host or base path of the API.
    For example, in /items/{itemId}, the path parameter is itemId
queryHint:
Parameters that are appended to the URL.
    For example, in /items?id=###, the query parameter is id
formDataHint:
Parameters that are submitted through a form.
    application/x-www-form-urlencoded, multipart/form-data or both are usually
    used as the content type of the request
headerHint: Custom headers that are expected as part of the request
